{"_id":"0XJBdVctDCnsrlYa","name":"For to Summon up a Mighty Wind","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell creates a wind that blows out ahead of the caster for as long as he Concentrates on the spell. The wind affects everything within an area 10 metres wide and 20 metres long, in front of the caster&rsquo;s outstretched hand. The wind has increasing effects based on the Magnitude as follows:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1758%; height: 64px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%; height: 16px;\">Magnitude&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%; height: 16px;\">Effect</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%; height: 16px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%; height: 16px;\">Candles are blown out.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%; height: 16px;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%; height: 16px;\">Ranged attacks at -10%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%; height: 16px;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%; height: 16px;\">Birds have trouble flying. Ranged&nbsp;attacks at -20%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%;\">Those affected must make an Opposed&nbsp;Athletics roll against the wind&rsquo;s Blowing&nbsp;skill of 50% or fall prone. Ranged attacks&nbsp;at -50%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%;\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%;\">As above, but the wind&rsquo;s Blowing skill is 70%. Ranged attacks impossible. Perception at -25% due to flying debris.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%;\">7</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%;\">Anyone or thing with SIZ less than 21&nbsp;automatically blown over. Perception at&nbsp;-50% due to flying debris.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%;\">Anyone with SIZ less than 50 flung into&nbsp;the air and suffers 2D6 damage.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Air)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":true,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"0kn3CXHbNgZrlPFd","name":"For the Ignition of the Fires of Passion","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Gives the target the Seduction skill, or adds to the skill if the target already has it, for one single Seduction attempt. At Magnitude 1, this spell gives the target the Seduction skill at base level (INT+CHA), or adds +10% to an existing skill; each increase in Magnitude adds another 10% to the skill. It cannot be stacked with any other spell effect bonuses.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"0l8ffj3eXv3RLTam","name":"For the Warming ofthe Mortal Frame","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target suffers no penalties to Fatigue tests from a cold environment while this spell is functioning. Each increase in Magnitude increases the Duration by 10 minutes. The spell also protects the target from one point of cold damage&nbsp; (magickal or mundane) for every point of Magnitude.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"0mK1ThZ3pr4ZcDH3","name":"For the Illumination of the Darkness","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Cast on a physical object (including living material), this spell causes the object to shed light across a 10 metre area of effect. The area is then considered to be illuminated. Note that only a 10 metre area around the target object is&nbsp; lluminated &ndash; everything outside the area of effect is not. This spell creates raw light, not a flame.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"18lSLV0ICt67H7ED","name":"For to Breathe Underwater","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the target to breathe water for the Duration of the effect. For every point of Magnitude, one additional person can be included in the spell. For to Breathe Underwater has no effect on the target&rsquo;s ability to breathe air.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Summon a Nearby Beast","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell can be used to summon any creature (wild or tame) within range, which the caster knows to be present. It will effect any non-humanoid creature with INT of 7 or less, and the creature will be naturally drawn to the place where the spell is cast &ndash; as soon as that spot is reached, the spell terminates. (Note that if the caster moves from the point where he or she cast the spell, the focus of the spell remains on the spot where the summoning took place). Anything that would interrupt the spell (a barrier, the call of a dog&rsquo;s master, the command of a horse&rsquo;s rider, etc.) will cause the spell to be&nbsp; broken. This spell can be useful when hunting, or when seeking a Familiar.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Resilience","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1UgE3GsGsyd8jcpV"}
{"name":"For to Clear a Path Through a Tangled Thicket","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to move through even the most tangled, thorny brush as if he were on an open road. For each additional point of Magnitude, he may bring one person with him.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1v8Kc1DkSiAeF0sS"}
{"_id":"2RzrYRNVpHTMO63p","name":"For to Discover (X)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Element: any</p>\n<p>This covers a family of spells that all operate in a similar fashion, allowing the caster to locate the closest target of the spell within its range. This effect is stopped by a thick substance such as metal, earth or stone that is at least one metre thick. The separate spells For to Discover are listed below and must be learned separately to use them.</p>\n<p>For to Discover an Enemy: Gives the location of the nearest creatures, of a number equal to the Magnitude of the spell, that intend to harm the caster.</p>\n<p>For to Discover Magick: Gives the location and identity of the nearest Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone, magickal potion, or active spell, including Witchcraft. In the case of a Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone, it will tell the caster how many Magick Points it contains.</p>\n<p>For to Discover a (Species): Each For to Discover a (Species) spell will give the location of the nearest creature of the specified species. Examples of this spell include For to Discover a Wolf, For to Discover a Horse and For to Discover a Sparrow.</p>\n<p>For to Discover(Substance): Each spell For to Discover (Substance) will give the location of the nearest substance of the specified type. Examples of this spell include For to Discover Coal, For to Discover Gold and For to Discover Wood.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Air)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":true,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Special","touch":false,"trigger":false,"spellLevel":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/renaissance/images/750px-1650_Jansson_Wind_Rose%2C_Anemographic_Chart%2C_or_Map_of_the_Winds_-_Geographicus_-_Anemographica-jannson-1650.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Inspire the Hands of Craftmanship","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell gives the target a +10% bonus per point of Magnitude to his or her next Craft skill test. It cannot stack with any other spell-effect bonuses.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3HfovTp0kCmLSXlH"}
{"name":"For to Enhance the Hands of Healing","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell grants the caster a +10% bonus per point of&nbsp; Magnitude to his or her next First Aid or Healing roll. It is a common spell among Galenic Healers.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3NZOisRNDUUXm5Lo"}
{"_id":"4NfUKrn6LB53Dzbx","name":"For to Drive a Hard Bargain","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target gains a +10% bonus to any Evaluate or Influence test used when evaluating, buying or selling goods or equipment.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"4Ona3YM53EWLUIrm","name":"For to Breathe Like Unto a Dragon","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>With this spell, the caster spits a stream of fire at his target. If the fire is not Dodged, it inflicts 1D8 points of heat damage. Armour Points are effective against this damage and it counts as both magickal and fire damage.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Dodge","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"54926al16bxA6S13","name":"For to Cause the Conflagration of a Blade","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For the Duration, the target weapon will deal 1D10 magickal fire damage on top of its normal damage. A weapon under the effects of For to Cause the Conflagration of a Blade cannot benefit from For to Sharpen a Blade.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":4,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6j4lwA5AWqqSK7Il","name":"For the Encouragement of a Fanatical Mind","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target of this spell will have all Close Combat skills increased by +20%, but may not attempt to Parry or cast spells. The target will also have its Dodge skill halved. The effects of this spell are automatically cancelled by the spell For the Invocation of Fear, and vice versa.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8Q8lEG65xFqedBld","name":"For to cast a Glamour","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude, this spell increases the target&rsquo;s CHA score by +2. A target cannot have its CHA increased in this way to more than twice its original CHA score.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8XBEXN4eAeydIJpn","name":"For the Shaping of (an elemental Type)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to shape the form of a previously summoned Elemental into any shape he wishes. The Elemental must be controlled within a circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone (see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details). The shape can be anything the caster can imagine, but can never be greater in size than the size in cubic metres of the Elemental summoned. The shaper must be within 5 metres of the Elemental when casting the spell.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For the summoning of a Gnome","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell must be learned separately for each of the four types of Elementals described in the Bestiary. The spell summons forth an Elemental of one cubic metre per point of Magnitude, which will manifest after 1D3 combat rounds. There must be enough of the element in question within five metres of the caster when the spell is cast; so a Gnome must be summoned close to Earth (an easy one unless the caster is several stories up in a building or is flying for some reason), a Salamander must be summoned close to a fire big enough to hold its mass, a&nbsp; Sylph must be summoned close to Air (almost anywhere except under water!) and an Undine close to a body of water big enough to hold its mass.</p>\n<p>Note that an Elemental is uncontrolled unless it has been summoned within a&nbsp; circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone &ndash; see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8i0jCxyHQIq11vpI"}
{"name":"for to Make a Club Mighty","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell can be cast on any crushing or smashing weapon, such as a club. For every point of Magnitude, it increases the chance to hit with the weapon by +10% and deals one point of extra damage. This extra damage is magickal and will affect creatures that can only be hurt by magick. The weapon&rsquo;s base damage remains non-magickal.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AMo4TMpe8vGm5FaR"}
{"_id":"Aaauc2GZIhWArj1o","name":"For to Increase Co-Ordination","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude of this spell, the target&rsquo;s DEX score increases by +2. A target&rsquo;s DEX cannot be increased in this way to more than twice the original DEX score.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Repair a Broken Object","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude, this spell repairs one&nbsp; hit point of damage to any one non-living target. The marks of repair will remain visible, unless an appropriate Craft test is made at the time of casting.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CDA3HFgd7uPHBHVa"}
{"name":"Fot to Multiply a Hurtling Missile","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>&nbsp;This spell is cast on a missile, such as a musket ball, cannonball, arrow, throwing knife, or spear; it is not cast on ranged weapon itself (the gun, bow, etc.). The missile remains &lsquo;charged&rsquo; for the Duration, after which the spell expires, whether or not it has been triggered yet.. A missile under the effects of the spell For to Multiply a Hurtling Missile cannot benefit from the spells For to Cause the Conflagration of a Hurtling Missile or For to Speed a Hurtling Missile.</p>\n<p>When the enchanted missile is fired/thrown, one additional magickal missile is created for every point of Magnitude. Each magickal missile&rsquo;s attack is rolled for separately and each does the same damage as the original (though they will not benefit from the character&rsquo;s damage modifier). Magickal missiles created through this spell will not cause critical hits, though the original missile can. Such magickal missiles will affect creatures that can only be hurt by magick.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":1,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"EwvbvlqGc1udxDld"}
{"name":"For to Cure a Disease or Counteract a Poison","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell cures the effects of any mundane disease or poison affecting the target; it also cures magickal ailments whose Potency is less than the Elemental Casting skill of the caster.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GfzOVo0PnQ72WhRU"}
{"_id":"GqhGO9h4gSsXkh6Z","name":"For to Conjure a Bolt from the Blue","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The caster can summon a lightning bolt from the heavens regardless of the weather. The bolt must strike a target outdoors in plain view. For to Conjure a Bolt from the Blue inflicts 3D6 points of damage, ignoring any Armour Points.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Dodge","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Kgs822NJn89hWgzZ","name":"For the Dismissal of a Salamander","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell may be cast against an Elemental of the correct type. It affects an Elemental of up to 1 cubic metre in size per point of Magnitude. Failure to Resist means that the Elemental disperses. It is often difficult to get close to an Elemental in order to dismiss it with this Touch spell. Some solutions to this are discussed in &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Bring the Touch of Death","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The caster&rsquo;s hand is charged with the touch of death for the Duration, after which the spell simply expires. Once the effect has been unleashed, the wielder&rsquo;s hand is no longer charged.</p>\n<p>Touching an unsuspecting target, or succeeding at an Unarmed Combat attack against a wary target, releases the spell&rsquo;s effect. If the Resilience test to Resist the effect is failed, the hit location touched immediately suffers a number of Hit Points equal to the target&rsquo;s Major Wound Level. (If the target is already on 0 or less Hit Points, the Major Wound will be a Grave Wound). If the Resilience test is a success, the target only loses a single hit point. Armour Points do not protect against this damage.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":1,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":5,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KibGag8N85CzcprD"}
{"_id":"Kq56ytR4oABefQP5","name":"For the Dismissal of Undine","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell may be cast against an Elemental of the correct type. It affects an Elemental of up to 1 cubic metre in size per point of Magnitude. Failure to Resist means that the Elemental disperses. It is often difficult to get close to an Elemental in order to dismiss it with this Touch spell. Some solutions to this are discussed in &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"LCNVz94Li0VEeAdA","name":"For to Soothe the Restless","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the target to sleep for 10 hours without being disturbed by bad dreams, annoying noises, the pain of wounds, gentle movement and so on. He or she can still be woken by vigorous shaking or a loud noise. The spell does not actually put the target to sleep, merely allows uninterrupted sleep. It is especially useful to help the healing of characters whose Hit Points are currently less than 0.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"LR9g4stS5LLjTqMg","name":"For the Shaping of a Sylph","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to shape the form of a previously summoned Elemental into any shape he wishes. The Elemental must be controlled within a circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone (see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details). The shape can be anything the caster can imagine, but can never be greater in size than the size in cubic metres of the Elemental summoned. The shaper must be within 5 metres of the Elemental when casting the spell.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"LhkIOtZbPIj0Q8wj","name":"For the Shaping of a Salamander","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to shape the form of a previously summoned Elemental into any shape he wishes. The Elemental must be controlled within a circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone (see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details). The shape can be anything the caster can imagine, but can never be greater in size than the size in cubic metres of the Elemental summoned. The shaper must be within 5 metres of the Elemental when casting the spell.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Disrupt the Body","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell literally pulls a target&rsquo;s body apart. The target will suffer [[1d6]]1D6 points of damage, ignoring any Armour Points, and may receive a Major Wound to a random hit location.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Resilience","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"My1YpOT262y2VxiV"}
{"_id":"Nh8jMJO2TPARCcCn","name":"For to Dispel a Pestilential Miasma","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell dispels a disease miasma, whether natural or created with the spell For to Create a Pestilential Miasma. The diameter of miasma dispelled is equal to 10 metres per point of Magnitude. If the area dispelled is less than the total area of the miasma, the miasma will contract over the next 1D4 hours, flowing toward its centre so that it remains a continuous area. See Rules and Systems for more details on disease miasmas.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":2,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Enhance the Performance of an Entertainer","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell gives the target a +10% bonus to their next skill test involving Dance, Sing or Play Instrument in a social situation in which they are performing for others. It cannot stack with any other spell effect bonuses.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PhoCFaxt01U0u3Ld"}
{"name":"For to Impart Great Might","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude, the target&rsquo;s STR score increases by +2. A target cannot have its STR increased in this way to more than twice its original STR score.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PnUvEMkbGei4vPGy"}
{"_id":"RQBS2pqoP9uppecU","name":"For to Impart Good fortune","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the target to re-roll their next failed skill test. The target can then choose which of the two rolls to use &ndash; so if the target does even worse on the second roll (for instance, getting a fumble where the previous roll was merely a failure) they may choose to keep the first roll. The target can only benefit from one casting of this spell at a time.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For the Shaping of a Gnome","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to shape the form of a previously summoned Elemental into any shape he wishes. The Elemental must be controlled within a circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone (see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details). The shape can be anything the caster can imagine, but can never be greater in size than the size in cubic metres of the Elemental summoned. The shaper must be within 5 metres of the Elemental when casting the spell.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"S0L8YxGcIW6m12vd"}
{"name":"For the Dismissal of a Gnome","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell may be cast against an Elemental of the correct type. It affects an Elemental of up to 1 cubic metre in size per point of Magnitude. Failure to Resist means that the Elemental disperses. It is often difficult to get close to an Elemental in order to dismiss it with this Touch spell. Some solutions to this are discussed in &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SMIxKFVKDAfBX2Lj"}
{"_id":"StI0qsoakdGTnMDU","name":"For the Summoning of  a Salamander","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell must be learned separately for each of the four types of Elementals described in the Bestiary. The spell summons forth an Elemental of one cubic metre per point of Magnitude, which will manifest after 1D3 combat rounds. There must be enough of the element in question within five metres of the caster when the spell is cast; so a Gnome must be summoned close to Earth (an easy one unless the caster is several stories up in a building or is flying for some reason), a Salamander must be summoned close to a fire big enough to hold its mass, a&nbsp; Sylph must be summoned close to Air (almost anywhere except under water!) and an Undine close to a body of water big enough to hold its mass.</p>\n<p>Note that an Elemental is uncontrolled unless it has been summoned within a&nbsp; circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone &ndash; see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Mend a Broken Body","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell will instantly heal a number of Hit Points equal to the target&rsquo;s Serious Wound Level. It will also negate the effects of one Serious or Grave Wound, as long as the target is still alive, reattaching severed limbs and the like, if the spell is cast within an hour of the wound being taken. The spell will not regrow lost limbs.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WdBui7jOMD8Tb8St"}
{"_id":"WpefpcQ9wWTyZAYn","name":"For to Reveal the Secrets of the Heart","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Allows the caster to know which Faction the target belongs to, and gives a measure of the target&rsquo;s Righteousness Points to the nearest 10 RPs (rounded up from the actual figure).</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Persistence","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"a6k1Fe3RGMnS2GQ0","name":"For the Dismissal of a Sylph","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell may be cast against an Elemental of the correct type. It affects an Elemental of up to 1 cubic metre in size per point of Magnitude. Failure to Resist means that the Elemental disperses. It is often difficult to get close to an Elemental in order to dismiss it with this Touch spell. Some solutions to this are discussed in &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Air)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aBA9GVKm2z5kJMIh","name":"for to Inflict Frostbite","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This attack spell allows the caster to freeze his target, dealing 1D6+3 [[1d6+3]] point of damage, ignoring any Armour Points, and possibly causing a Major Wound. Magickal effects that protect against cold damage can block this effect, but mundane items are ineffective.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aHLumHs2WgwGzsDa","name":"For to Increase Alacrity","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude of this spell, the target&rsquo;s Movement score will be increased by one metre.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aP2EyNuaW50ADWpz","name":"For to Meddle with the Fate of Another","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to influence fate, either for the good or ill of the target. The caster can increase or decrease the target&rsquo;s next skill test by 10% for each point of Magnitude. Only the next skill test made after the spell&rsquo;s casting is affected.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"Persistence","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aX1jE1tXlW2NwX8x","name":"For to Impart Stealth","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell gives the target +10% to their next Stealth skill test involving hiding, lurking, following, etc. It cannot be stacked with any other spell-effect bonuses.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bLWDL541nMeGuLDQ","name":"For to Cause the Conflagration of a hurtling Missle","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Casting this spell on a missile weapon, arrow, crossbow bolt, pistol/musket ball or cannonball will cause it to burst into flame when it strikes a target. When it hits a target, the missile will deal 1D10 points of magickal fire damage on top of its normal damage. A missile under the effects of For to Cause the Conflagration of a Hurtling Missile cannot benefit from For to Multiply a Hurtling Missile or For to Speed a Hurtling Missile.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":1,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bjqkfAw7T3sz1YmR","name":"For the Dismissal of (an Elemental Type)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell may be cast against an Elemental of the correct type. It affects an Elemental of up to 1 cubic metre in size per point of Magnitude. Failure to Resist means that the Elemental disperses. It is often difficult to get close to an Elemental in order to dismiss it with this Touch spell. Some solutions to this are discussed in &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"c1O1QxtYFYJClAGu","name":"For to Part the Clouds","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell makes a break in any cloud cover, allowing the sun or moon and stars to shine through. It does not alter the temperature. The diameter of the clear sky is equal to 10 metres per point of Magnitude. Any rain, snow, fog, etc. is&nbsp; negated by the spell. The spell effect is centred on the target, and moves with him as he travels. The spell cannot alter magickally-created weather effects of greater Magnitude.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"d2BE5q3sNxQkUkOW","name":"For the Domination of a Familiar(Species)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell gives the caster control over a specific type of non-human creature for the purposes of using it as a Familiar (see the Familiar rules later in this chapter). Each species is a different spell, so<em> For the Domination of a Familiar Dog </em>must be learned separately from<em> For the Domination of a Familiar Cat</em>.</p>\n<p>The caster may attempt to dominate a target of up to 3 INT per 1 Magnitude. If the target fails to Resist, it must obey the caster while the spell lasts.</p>\n<p>The controlled Familiar shares a limited telepathic link with the caster by which it can receive orders; it is completely in thrall to the wishes of the caster and can even be made to take its own life if the caster so wishes. If the Familiar is currently carrying a spell, the spell can be cast with a simple mental command.</p>\n<p>The caster cannot use the senses of the Familiar, so must be able to see the creature if he wants to be sure what it is doing.</p>\n<p>Due to the degree of control exerted on the creature, many Alchemists consider this spell unethical &ndash; it treats an animal as an unfeeling mechanism, something more common among the Mechanical Philosophers of the Parliamentarian cause than anything the average Royalist would espouse.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":true,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"Persistence","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"eMFJ3Buf2BihsHWd","name":"For to Create a Weapon Against Ghosts","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Cast on an item (normally a gun, missile weapon or close combat weapon), this spell allows it to temporarily exist both in the real world and the spirit world. As such, the item can affect ghosts. Damage done to a ghost is taken off its POW; once it&rsquo;s POW&nbsp;reaches zero, the ghost vanishes &ndash; whether it has been</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For the Uplift of the Weary","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude, this spell will restore one level of Fatigue the target is currently suffering from.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"eeErUx2b6nzN1jyD"}
{"name":"For to Sharpen a Blade","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell can be cast on any weapon with a blade. For every point of Magnitude, it increases the chance to hit with the weapon by +10% and deals one point of extra damage. This extra damage is magickal and will affect creatures that can only be hurt by magick. The weapon&rsquo;s base damage remains non-magickal. A weapon under the effects of the spell For to Sharpen a Blade cannot benefit from the spell For to to Cause the Conflagration of a Blade.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fcNmjZ4o3LNgirB8"}
{"_id":"hU2uqqT1lDhi9376","name":"For to Steady the Hands of a Marksman","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell doubles the target&rsquo;s aim bonus the next time they spend (or attempt to spend) at least one round aiming a gun or other ranged weapon, so that aiming for one round will give a +40% bonus, aiming for two rounds will give a +80% bonus, etc. However, if the marksman&rsquo;s aim is interrupted before the shot is fired, the spell&rsquo;s effect is lost.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For Enhancing the Performance of an Entertainer","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell gives the target a +10% bonus to their next skill test involving Dance, Sing or Play Instrument in a social situation in which they are performing for others. It cannot stack with any other spell effect bonuses.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"i0KqeuPlmrF9jUMM"}
{"name":"For to Create a Healing Bouquet","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell creates a pleasant, flowery aroma that facilitates healing. The diameter of the aroma is equal to 10 metres per point of Magnitude. Anyone within the cloud of aroma gains a +25% to their Resilience for the purposes of regaining Hit Points from Natural Healing and for making Resilience rolls to Resist against ongoing poisons and diseases. A spell For to Create a Healing Bouquet cast within a disease miasma does not dispel the miasma, but does add +25% to Resilience tests to avoid contracting the disease.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":24,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iaNE965dTho4wFvm"}
{"_id":"ikbV7D01vEcCcDC5","name":"For the Ignition of a Consuming Flame","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell will set fire to anything readily flammable within range. Skin or flesh cannot be ignited, and if the target is attached to a living being (such as hair, fur or clothes) then the spell gains the Resist (Resilience) trait.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lL6H6N9ro5tnaJL6","name":"For to Fling Far the Hurtling Missile","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Cast on a gun, cannon or other ranged weapon, this spell doubles the Range of the weapon for the Duration.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":1,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lSA1jv3weHHcf8ji","name":"For to Call the Creative Muse","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell gives the target a +10% bonus per point of Magnitude to his or her next Art skill roll. It cannot stack with any other spell-effect bonuses.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ldLzD6H6cYpNka4l","name":"For to cause a Great Downpour","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell causes clouds to boil up out of a clear sky and a heavy rain to fall. The diameter of the area caught in the downpour is equal to 10 metres per point of Magnitude. The rain is very heavy; it can cause localised flooding, and turn open ground to slippery mud, reducing Movement Rate by a quarter and bogging down carts and heavy machinery. Anyone not wearing waterproof clothing will be soaked to the skin. Any guns or cannon will fail to fire while the downpour lasts, unless they are under cover. All Perception skills are halved within the area of the spell. The rain is centred on the caster and moves with him when he travels. The spell cannot alter magickally-created weather effects of greater Magnitude.</p>\n<p>An Alchemist within a downpour caused by this spell can use the spell For the Summoning of an Undine spell to summon an Undine even if there are no large bodies of water nearby.</p>\n<p>If the temperature is below freezing, the rain will still fall as rain, but will freeze as soon as the spell ends, coating&nbsp; everything in a thick layer of ice and reducing Movement Rate in that area by three quarters until the ice is cleared or the weather turns warmer.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mGANnsgJYQyYk8UT","name":"For to Cause Slowness","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude of this spell, the target&rsquo;s Movement score will be decreased by one metre. A target&rsquo;s Movement may not be reduced to below one metre through use of this spell.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":true,"resist":"Resilience","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Protect Against the Blows of the enemy","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude, this spell adds one Armour Point to the target. This stacks with any existing armour and is treated in the same way.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mmAWyqcsplwIzGzr"}
{"_id":"nu1zf3okpfvlRR36","name":"For to Understand Another","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude, this spell gives the target +10% to any Language skill he already knows.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"oAg1YX4qaqesrEKG","name":"For the Invocation of a Great Darkness","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Light sources within this Area shed no light and normal sight ceases to function. Other senses such as a bat&rsquo;s sonar function normally.</p>","skill":"0","area":5,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"pASWkdbzwuDE1QP8","name":"For to Cool an Object","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell can be used to cool down an object &ndash; whether that be a recently made potion, a tray of drinks in a tavern, etc. The spell cannot be used to actually freeze anything, and it is not possible to cause physical harm. The Games Master should adjudicate what can and cannot be done with this spell in any given situation.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Impart Vigour","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude, the target&rsquo;s CON score increases by +2. A target cannot have its CON increased in this way to more than twice its original CON score.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pNSsaEamMe1hqyEN"}
{"_id":"phPYZjb7jadf6H7g","name":"For to Increase the Defences of the Beleaguered Warrior","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Cast on a Close Combat weapon, this spell adds +10% to the weapon-bearer&rsquo;s Close Combat skill when parrying with that weapon. Each point of Magnitude adds +10% to the fighter&rsquo;s parry.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"pmgK9PUOMwU5Nlk5","name":"For to Count Many Things","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This allows the caster to accurately count a great number of similar things that are together in a mass &ndash; sacks of grain, muskets in an armoury, pikemen in an army. The caster must be able to see what is being counted and very precisely say what he is counting, otherwise the result may not be accurate. For instance, asking for &ldquo;the number of people in the enemy camp&rdquo; would include all the camp-followers, servants, etc., while asking for &ldquo;the number of soldier in the enemy camp&rdquo; would include any prisoners-of-war, and so on.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"systems/renaissance/images/462px-Houghton_Typ_520.03.736_-_Margarita_philosophica.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Fight like unto a Wild Beast","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target&rsquo;s Unarmed Combat attacks are considered natural weapons and for every point of Magnitude, it increases the chance to hit with the target&rsquo;s natural weapons by +10% and deals one point of extra damage. This extra damage is magickal and will affect creatures that can only be hurt by magick. The base natural weapon damage remains non-magickal.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qX6nlXQ4LpPlmPed"}
{"_id":"qcLbzmc01AE6fOPE","name":"For to See Through the Eyes of Another","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Cast on a living creature (human or animal), this spell allows the caster to see through the eyes of that creature for 5 minutes per point of Magnitude. The caster has no control over what the target looks at, but if the creature has Night Sight, he gains that ability through the eyes of the creature. While this spell is in effect, the caster is blind to anything his own eyes would normally see, but can hear, smell, taste and feel as normal, and can dismiss the spell instantly if he feels the need to see. A target who wants the caster to see through his eyes need not Resist. Familiars that have been calmed with the Lore (Animal) skill or the Dominate Familiar spell will not Resist either.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"Persistence","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Bond Together Disparate Things","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell causes an object of up to 3 SIZ per 1 Magnitude to merge with a contacting surface for 24 hours or until the spell is dismissed. The binding is unbreakable by normal means, save for the destruction of the target or the surface it is bonded to.</p>\n<p>The spell can be used on inanimate or living targets; however, if the caster attempts to bond a living being, or anything it is holding or wearing, the spell may be Resisted with the Resilience skill.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":24,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rrmKMDwFsRI1lhzS"}
{"_id":"tmdsDUaZLRz6ByTf","name":"For to Speak unto the Mind of Another","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell can affect one target for every point of Magnitude. It allows telepathy between the caster and any target, though targets will not have telepathy with one another. The words transmitted by telepathy must be whispered and will be heard directly in the head of the recipient(s), in the same language in which they were spoken.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Cause a Person to Speak with Authority","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude of this spell, the target will have +10% added to his Influence skill. The target&rsquo;s voice may also be heard at up to the spell&rsquo;s Magnitude x 100 in metres.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ttwkQjQQQObbZjNg"}
{"_id":"uvEsjx2YHEVW19LI","name":"For to Cause a preson to Speak with Authority","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude of this spell, the target will have +10% added to his Influence skill. The target&rsquo;s voice may also be heard at up to the spell&rsquo;s Magnitude x 100 in metres.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Air)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Pierce the Armour of a Foe","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell can be cast on any weapon with a blade or point. For every point of Magnitude, it ignores one Armour Point when it strikes an armoured location. The spell can bypass magickal armour as easily as normal armour.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"v5wybLC7Po837j4Y"}
{"_id":"vGLUL7LynpW8go5L","name":"For to Raise a Great Fog","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell creates a thick fog that obscures all vision and muffles hearing. The diameter of the fog is equal to 10 metres per point of Magnitude. Anyone in the fog (including the caster!) has their Perception skill reduced by half. The fog is centred on the caster, and moves with him as he travels. The spell cannot alter magickally-created weather effects of greater Magnitude.</p>\n<p>Because the fog is made of elemental water, it cannot be dispersed by a normal wind, no matter how strong, but only by an elemental wind of greater Magnitude, caused by the spell For to Create a Mighty Wind. An Alchemist within an elemental fog can use the spell For the Summoning of an Undine to summon an Undine even if there are no large bodies of water nearby.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vjqBGvzPA1MGQVXU","name":"For the Confusion of the Tongue","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>If this spell is successful, it garbles the language of the affected person. The target can still think and, for the most part, act normally, but anything it says comes out as gibberish.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Persistence","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vslpS0Tt4b6yDfMa","name":"For the summoning of (an Elemental Type)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell must be learned separately for each of the four types of Elementals described in the Bestiary. The spell summons forth an Elemental of one cubic metre per point of Magnitude, which will manifest after 1D3 combat rounds. There must be enough of the element in question within five metres of the caster when the spell is cast; so a Gnome must be summoned close to Earth (an easy one unless the caster is several stories up in a building or is flying for some reason), a Salamander must be summoned close to a fire big enough to hold its mass, a&nbsp; Sylph must be summoned close to Air (almost anywhere except under water!) and an Undine close to a body of water big enough to hold its mass.</p>\n<p>Note that an Elemental is uncontrolled unless it has been summoned within a&nbsp; circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone &ndash; see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vtrUsbM5QfhnASN6","name":"For the Befuddlement of the Mind","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The affected target may not cast spells and may only take non-offensive actions. The target may run if it so chooses and may Dodge and Parry normally in combat, though it may not make any attacks. If the target is directly attacked, the spell is cancelled and the target is free to retaliate.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Persistence","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vvSUrlYuKAYfKaO6","name":"For the Shaping of Undine","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to shape the form of a previously summoned Elemental into any shape he wishes. The Elemental must be controlled within a circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone (see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details). The shape can be anything the caster can imagine, but can never be greater in size than the size in cubic metres of the Elemental summoned. The shaper must be within 5 metres of the Elemental when casting the spell.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"wqXgPyU74OUR74xf","name":"For to Extinguish a conflagration","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell instantly puts out fires. At Magnitude 1, it can extinguish a Flame, Magnitude 2 a Small Fire, Magnitude 3 a Large Fire and Magnitude 4 will put out an Inferno. (See Rules and Systems for the definition of these different sorts of fires).</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Water)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"xi3fKLgIjka6qUEP","name":"For the Invocation of Fear","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target of this spell has all combat skills halved and may not cast offensive spells. If this spell takes effect before combat begins, the target will try to avoid fighting and will either run or surrender. The effects of this spell are&nbsp; automatically cancelled by the spell for the Encouragement of a Fanatical Mind and vice versa.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Fire)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Persistence","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"yELyozWTmDcNtu5I","name":"For the Summoning of  a Sylph","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell must be learned separately for each of the four types of Elementals described in the Bestiary. The spell summons forth an Elemental of one cubic metre per point of Magnitude, which will manifest after 1D3 combat rounds. There must be enough of the element in question within five metres of the caster when the spell is cast; so a Gnome must be summoned close to Earth (an easy one unless the caster is several stories up in a building or is flying for some reason), a Salamander must be summoned close to a fire big enough to hold its mass, a&nbsp; Sylph must be summoned close to Air (almost anywhere except under water!) and an Undine close to a body of water big enough to hold its mass.</p>\n<p>Note that an Elemental is uncontrolled unless it has been summoned within a&nbsp; circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone &ndash; see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"yZGwXYjzjnEU7jSW","name":"For the Creation of a Pestilential Miasma","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell creates a disease-causing miasma. The diameter of the miasma is equal to 10 metres per point of Magnitude. Anyone within the miasma must make an opposed Resilience test against the Potency of the disease or immediately&nbsp; contract it (this includes the caster!). Each disease is a different spell, which must be learned separately. See Rules and Systems for more details on disease miasmas.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Air)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":24,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Decrease the Potency of a Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell can be cast on any crafted weapon, but will not affect unarmed attacks or natural weaponry. For every point of Magnitude, it reduces the damage dealt by the target weapon by one.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"z9WTNfhYiIQ3dkpI"}
{"name":"For to Bring the Touch of Healing","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude of this spell, the castercan repair one Hit Point of damage to either himself</p>\n<p>or another target.</p>\n<p>A Magnitude 6 or higher spell for to Bring the Touch of Healing will also negate the effects of a Major Wound (Serious or Grave) as long as the target is still alive, reattaching severed limbs and the like, as long as it is performed within 6 combat rounds of the wound being taken. It will not resurrect a character, whether they have been killed by a fatal Grave Wound or a fatal loss of Hit Points, nor will it regrow lost limbs.</p>\n<p>A Magnitude 8 or higher Heal spell will also cure any single poison or disease affecting the target.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Earth)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zdFvX8rluJWwjEpW"}
